article.description: Evan Boudreaux scored a career high-tying 25 points and Dartmouth set a school scoring record, crushing Division III member Pine Manor 121-56 on Saturday.
article.headline: Dartmouth sets program records against Pine Manor 121-56
article.linkText: Dartmouth sets program records against Pine Manor 121-56
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Evan Boudreaux scored a career high-tying 25 points and Dartmouth set a school scoring record, crushing Division III member Pine Manor 121-56 on Saturday. Dartmouth set program records for points and field goals made (50). The Big Green outrebounded the Gators 59-17, had 29 assists and made 11 steals. Boudreaux was 11 of 14 from the floor with seven rebounds for Dartmouth (6-9). The freshman has led Dartmouth in scoring in eight of 15 games and is currently tied for fourth in scoring average for a freshman in Ivy League history (15.8). Connor Boehm scored 12 points with nine rebounds, leaving him just 23 points short of becoming the 28th player in program history to record 1,000 points. Wesley Dickinson had 14 points while Guilien Smith and Cameron Smith added 11 points apiece as Dartmouth shot over 63 percent. Pine Manor, in just its second season, fields only freshmen and sophomores. Taverick Roberson led the Gators with 11 points.
